Nigerian superstars, PSquare, Wizkid, Davido, alongside American R and B Superstar,Chris Brown, American Rapper,Megan Thee Stallion, Dancehall Star,Beenieman,are set to perform at AfroNation 2022. Other entertainers billed to perform at one of the world’s biggest Afrobeats festivals are Afro B, Wande Coal, Ckay, Tems, Diamond Platnumz, Koffee, Naira Marley, Rema, Tekno, Tems, Patoranking, Olamide, Yemi Alade among others stars who will bring their influence to the event. The festival, which is returning this year after a two year break, is scheduled to hold in two regions. The first phase will take place between March 24, 2022 and March 26, 2022, in Balneario de Carolina, Puerto Rico, American while the second edition will take place on the Praia da Rocha beach in Portimo, Algarve, from July 1, 2022 to July 3, 2022. According to the organisers, the event had two previous editions postponed as a result of the global COVID-19 pandemic, but is returning this year with what they described “landmark” iteration. AfroNation is a music event that promotes Afrobeats, hip-hop, Afrohouse, Amapiano, dancehall, R&B, and other genres.